reviews.review_text:
Sweet stuff I'm biased. I was born on this day, and I used to listen to my tape of it constantly, it was one of my first bootlegs. A steady rocker with some sweet surprises. The setlist, in my mind, is convincing enough for a download. Mission in the Rain is a quintessential trip into Jerry's soulful singing and  it surprised me when I found it to be seldom played.
No other song is worth singling out from the others, tt's a really good, complete, gem of a Dead show.

friend of the Piano Player Friend of the devil is sweet, I will always long for the days when they played if fast and aqustic in 1970, when jerry's voice was so ripe that nobody noticed his reduced strings on the tune, But keith's opening melody is burned in my mind, this is the peak renewed version of the song, some songs are lucky to peak once!!!

the best copy. I strongly disagree with the reviewer of the hand held mikes copy. This copy of the show is much more realistic. The hand held show sounds like it has the middle frequencies tweeked with some eq boost. This copy is well balanced.

What a jem!!! Love these setlists from this era.  The band was tight into some kickin exploration.  Cant say I like much better than earlier or even the following couple but it great GD none the less.
